00:04:56.180 --> 00:05:00.680
like wanting to learn a new
language or stick with things.

00:05:00.680 --> 00:05:03.410
They also apply to business.

00:05:03.410 --> 00:05:09.170
So a team in your organization
may have plans to complete work

00:05:09.170 --> 00:05:11.940
by a deadline.

00:05:11.940 --> 00:05:15.070
But then they keep
missing their deadlines.

00:05:15.070 --> 00:05:18.860
But they plan their
own deadlines.

00:05:18.860 --> 00:05:22.780
Now the typical solution
to things like this,

00:05:22.780 --> 00:05:25.660
or the reasoning
behind it, is to say

00:05:25.660 --> 00:05:30.310
that the person is flawed,
that the person doesn't have

00:05:30.310 --> 00:05:33.430
enough willpower, the person
isn't motivated enough,

00:05:33.430 --> 00:05:35.220
and we need to
change the person.

00:05:35.220 --> 00:05:39.280
But that not only makes us
feel badly about ourselves

00:05:39.280 --> 00:05:43.030
as people with putting
blame like that,

00:05:43.030 --> 00:05:47.230
but it's not the
correct science.

00:05:47.230 --> 00:05:50.260
So what I've learned
is that we just

00:05:50.260 --> 00:05:53.050
need to know that
there are three

00:05:53.050 --> 00:05:55.990
different types of behaviors.

00:05:55.990 --> 00:05:59.150
Once we know those three
different types of behaviors,

00:05:59.150 --> 00:06:01.510
there are a set of
tools for changing

00:06:01.510 --> 00:06:04.280
those three types of behaviors.

00:06:04.280 --> 00:06:07.030
So that's what we're going
to go over in this talk.

00:06:07.030 --> 00:06:08.710
